    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-11-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="357"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d357">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102S/1368</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 30</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-11-12">November 12,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the Legation’s despatch No. 3757 of
                    August 20, 1935,<note n="32" xml:id="d357fn32">Not printed.</note> and to
                    previous correspondence in regard to the Shanghai Defense Scheme, the Department
                    concurs in the opinion expressed by you that no useful purpose would be served
                    by proceeding further toward obtaining the revision of Part II, Paragraph 4, of
                    the Defense Scheme as suggested by the Department.</p>
                <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
